The paper deals with the problem of fine-grained image recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves deep learning and end-to-end training, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of classifiers and decision boundaries, which are concepts from natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
